finbreak (0.1.17) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Flatpak + native Linux packages (RPM/deb) — install finbreak via GNOME
    Software, KDE Discover, or your distro's package manager.
  * Categories can now be organised three levels deep (Type > Category >
    Sub-category), with rename, move and delete at every level.
  * "Report an Issue" menu item; signed SHA256SUMS checksums and per-platform
    software-component lists (SBOMs) for independent release verification.
  * Forgotten-password vault reset on the unlock screen, and a "Verify backup"
    button in Settings that checks a backup is readable before you rely on it.
  * Amounts show the currency symbol ("R 1,234.49") with a dedicated Currency
    column; confirmed transfers now show directionally on the Transactions tab.
  * Optional password hint on the unlock screen; copied amounts/descriptions
    auto-clear from the clipboard; repeated wrong unlock attempts are throttled.

 -- Anthony Schemel <aant.schemel@gmail.com>  Thu, 23 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

finbreak (0.1.16) unstable; urgency=medium

  * OFX import now files each transaction under the date the bank printed, even
    when the statement carries a timezone.
  * The delete-statement confirmation no longer over-states the loss when the
    statement overlaps another one you keep.
  * Deleting a statement no longer loses transactions that an overlapping
    statement still covers — they are handed over to the statement you keep.

 -- Anthony Schemel <aant.schemel@gmail.com>  Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200
